<text top="126" left="57" width="200" height="16" font="5"><b>RIDER, CHRISTIAN PAUL</b></text>
<text top="90" left="694" width="75" height="15" font="4"><b>201404611</b></text>
<text top="167" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>pointed at the man talking on the phone and told me that he was the suspect. I asked to speak with</b></text>
<text top="182" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>a manager and exited the store to speak with Rider. Outside the store I attempted to get Rider`s</b></text>
<text top="197" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>attention at least three times by saying &#34;sir&#34;. Rider seemed to ignore me and continued to talk on</b></text>
<text top="213" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>the phone. I stood by Rider while he continued his phone conversation. Approximately 30 seconds</b></text>
<text top="228" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>later the manager,  Michelle Penycuff walked outside towards me and Rider. When Penycuff got near</b></text>
<text top="243" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>myself and Rider he told me he was talking with the &#34; owner of McDonalds&#34;. Rider then attempted to</b></text>
<text top="259" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>hand me his phone to speak with the &#34;owner&#34;. I told Rider that I did not wish to speak with the</b></text>
<text top="274" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>owner. I began to talk with the manager to figure out what had happened inside the store. Penycuff</b></text>
<text top="289" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>explained that Rider had come through the drive through and paid for his  order. Penycuff told me</b></text>
<text top="305" left="64" width="745" height="11" font="8"><b>that Rider had then come inside the store and told her that he was shorted $14.00 in change.</b></text>
<text top="320" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>Penycuff started to explain Rider`s actions inside the store. Penycuff told me that Rider was</b></text>
<text top="335" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>yelling and attempted to come behind the counter. Penycuff also said that Rider`s behavior was</b></text>
<text top="351" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>&#34;scaring&#34; customers. As Penycuff was telling her account of the incident Rider walked over to</b></text>
<text top="366" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>myself and Penycuff and interrupted and started to talk loudly and point. I asked Rider to allow</b></text>
<text top="381" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>Penycuff to finish her statement and I would speak with him. Rider continued to talk loudly and I</b></text>
<text top="397" left="64" width="745" height="11" font="8"><b>was unable to hear Penycuff. I asked Rider again to stop interrupting and to walk over to my</b></text>
<text top="412" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>patrol vehicle so that I could finish my conversation with Penycuff. Rider refused and walked</b></text>
<text top="427" left="64" width="745" height="11" font="8"><b>within arms reach of me and continued to talk loudly to me. Rider was explaining that he had</b></text>
<text top="443" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>talked to the owner and that he wanted his money back. During the conversation rider began to</b></text>
<text top="458" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>point and talk loudly to me. Rider`s hand was within 6 inches of my face. Rider seemed angry and I</b></text>
<text top="473" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>did not feel comfortable with him being so close to me. I wished to create a reactionary distance</b></text>
<text top="489" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>and asked Rider to lower his hands and step back away from me. Rider complied with my request but</b></text>
<text top="504" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>continued to speak loudly preventing me from holding a conversation with Penycuff. I directed</b></text>
<text top="519" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>Rider to stand at the trunk of my patrol vehicle so that I could hear Penycuff but he refused to</b></text>
<text top="535" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>go to my patrol vehicle. I attempted to ask Penycuff if any threats were made and Rider raised his</b></text>
<text top="550" left="64" width="713" height="11" font="8"><b>voice again. I asked Rider to lower his voice again and he asked me &#34; what gives you the</b></text>
<text top="565" left="64" width="721" height="11" font="8"><b>authority&#34;. I attempted to explain to Rider that I was investigating a disturbance but he</b></text>
<text top="581" left="64" width="729" height="11" font="8"><b>continued to talk over me. Rider was still within 5 feet of me and placed his hands in his</b></text>
<text top="596" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>pockets. Because of Riders demeanor I asked Rider to remove his hands from his pockets and he</b></text>
<text top="611" left="64" width="737" height="11" font="8"><b>complied. Rider then began to yell and told me he did not have to remove his hands from his</b></text>
<text top="627" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>pockets. Rider began to walk to his vehicle and I told him to stop. Rider then told me that I</b></text>
<text top="642" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>could not order him to stop and asked if he was under arrest. I told Rider that he was not under</b></text>
<text top="658" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>arrest but informed him that he was detained until I could determine if any threats or assaults</b></text>
<text top="673" left="64" width="737" height="11" font="8"><b>had occurred in the incident. Rider again told me that I could not make him stay. Rider was</b></text>
<text top="688" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>becoming more upset as the conversation continued. I told Rider to stay back from me, keep his</b></text>
<text top="704" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>hands away from my face, keep his hands away from his pockets and allow me to speak with Penycuff.</b></text>
<text top="719" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>I turned to speak with speak with Penycuff again and he immediately started yelling and raised</b></text>
<text top="734" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>his left towards my face pointing his finger and lowered his right hand towards his pocket.  I had</b></text>
<text top="750" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>already told Rider once to keep his hands from his pockets. Rider was becoming more upset and</b></text>
<text top="765" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>yelling louder. Because of Riders demeanor and his refusal to keep his hands out of his pockets</b></text>
<text top="780" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>and his refusal to allow me to speak with Penycuff I made the decision to detain him until I could</b></text>
<text top="796" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>call for backup. I ordered Rider to place his hands behind his back and he complied.I was able to</b></text>
<text top="811" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>handcuff him without further incident. I attempted to explain why I had detained him and that It</b></text>
<text top="826" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>was temporary but he continued to yell and interrupt me. I walked Rider to the rear of my patrol</b></text>
<text top="842" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>vehicle so that I could sit him in the back seat and continue my investigation. At the back door</b></text>
<text top="857" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>Rider said &#34; Im not sitting in the back seat&#34;. I opened the door and Rider refused to sit down.</b></text>
<text top="872" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>Rider demanded that I contact a supervisor. I asked Rider to sit in the back seat again and he</b></text>
<text top="888" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>refused. Rider Turned around and faced me and attempted to side step past me towards my trunk. I</b></text>
<text top="903" left="64" width="745" height="11" font="8"><b>placed my hand on his shoulder to prevent him from walking away.  Rider then started to push</b></text>
<text top="918" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>against me  began to walk to the trunk of the car. I told Rider to stop pushing and turned his</b></text>
<text top="934" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>body towards my patrol vehicle so that I could control him if he continued to resist. I placed my</b></text>
<text top="949" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>left knee between his legs and leaned against him to prevent him from pulling away. I used my body</b></text>
<text top="964" left="64" width="745" height="11" font="8"><b>weight to hold Rider against the vehicle and told him to stop pushing away. Rider demanded a</b></text>
<text top="980" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>supervisor again and I told him I would contact one. Rider stopped resisting and I contacted Sgt</b></text>
<text top="995" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>Triplett. I asked Rider again to sit in the back seat and he refused. Rider said he had a medical</b></text>
<text top="1010" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>condition and could not sit in a back seat. Rather than use force to sit him in the back seat I</b></text>
<text top="1026" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>asked him if he would be more comfortable sitting on the curb. Rider said again he wasn`t sitting</b></text>
<text top="1041" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>in the back of the car so I walked him over to a outdoor table and asked him to sit down. Rider</b></text>
<text top="1056" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>complied and I waited for Sgt Triplett to arrive on scene. Rider attempted to get up and I ordered</b></text>
<text top="1072" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>him to remain sitting. Rider complied for approximately 30 seconds and attempted to stand again</b></text>
<text top="1087" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>and reach into his right pocket while handcuffed. I ordered Rider again to stop and sit down and</b></text>
<text top="1116" left="45" width="187" height="11" font="9"><i>Arrest Report (Additional Narrative)</i></text>
