<text top="90" left="694" width="75" height="15" font="4"><b>201404611</b></text>
<text top="162" left="64" width="778" height="11" font="8"><b>he demanded that I make a phone call for him. Rider complied and continued to sit down until Sgt</b></text>
<text top="178" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>Triplett arrived. Pso Miller and Sgt Triplett arrived on scene and Pso Miller stood by with Rider</b></text>
<text top="193" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>so that I could continue the investigation. Sgt Triplett spoke with Rider while I continued my</b></text>
<text top="208" left="64" width="737" height="11" font="8"><b>investigation and took down names of witnesses. After my investigation Sgt Triplett checked</b></text>
<text top="224" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>surveillance video while I stood with Rider. Rider began to complain of a heart condition and</b></text>
<text top="239" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>asked for EMS. I contacted EMS and informed Rider that they were on their way. Rider then told me</b></text>
<text top="254" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>that he was not going to get into the ambulance and that we would have to force him to get into</b></text>
<text top="270" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>the truck. Rider ordered me to remove the handcuffs because they were causing him to have heart</b></text>
<text top="285" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>problems. Because of Rider`s behavior the handcuff`s were not removed. EMS arrived a short time</b></text>
<text top="300" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>later and EMS staff began to speak with Rider. Rider was talking loudly with EMS staff and refused</b></text>
<text top="316" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>to allow them to speak. EMS staff attempted several times to speak with Rider but he would not</b></text>
<text top="331" left="64" width="737" height="11" font="8"><b>allow them to speak. After several attempts to speak with Rider EMS staff left the scene. I</b></text>
<text top="346" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>continued to stand by with Rider while Sgt Triplett investigated the incident. While standing with</b></text>
<text top="362" left="64" width="753" height="11" font="8"><b>Rider he told me that if he were to really be mad I would not still be standing. Rider walked</b></text>
<text top="377" left="64" width="721" height="11" font="8"><b>close to me and repeated the statement while standing approximately three feet from me. I</b></text>
<text top="392" left="64" width="761" height="11" font="8"><b>explained to Rider again that Sgt Triplett was investigation the incident and he would be done</b></text>
<text top="408" left="64" width="794" height="11" font="8"><b>shortly. Approximately 15 minutes later Sgt Triplett walked out of the store and spoke with Rider.</b></text>
<text top="423" left="64" width="769" height="11" font="8"><b>Sgt Triplett then spoke with me about the incident. Triplett and I made the decision to issue a</b></text>
<text top="438" left="64" width="786" height="11" font="8"><b>citation for Resist Obstruct and Delay and release Rider so that he could seek medical treatment.</b></text>
<text top="454" left="64" width="332" height="11" font="8"><b>Rider was issued a citation and released.</b></text>
